# GO wth cluster 6 identifies mitotic cell. Markers of cell cycle regulators Cdk1, proliferation marker MKI67, and cyclin marker CCNB1 are all enriched in cluster 6. This suggests that these cells are actively proliferating, and currently undergoing mitosis. These cells could be cells undergoing differentiation and at the mitotic clonal expansion stage (48 h for human adipogenesis: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5662072/#s013title), or preadipocytes proliferating, that never responded to the induction media. However, cells in cluster 6 exhibit the expression of CEBPA, which is only induced in response to IM. Cells in cluster 0 are at more advanced stage of differentiation, as marked by higher PPARG expression and GO analysis. Therefore, it will be interesting to see if these cells in cluster 6 would cluster with day 0 preadipocytes, day 5 preadipocytes, or somewhere in between.
